                                                                                                                       7                                                                                                      
	Karachi: The Pakistan Cricket Board chairman Ijaz Butt defended the punishments imposed on seven top players, saying strong action was needed to stamp out indiscipline in the national side.    
	Calcutta: The ICC chief executives rsquo; committee met in Dubai on Tuesday and Wednesday. The chief executive rsquo;s committee received an update on the successful implementation of the decision review system in 14 Test matches in the past four months.    
	Calcutta: The ICC announced on Thursday that Andy Pycroft, and not Jeff Crowe (as was mentioned in a release on Wednesday), has been selected as a Match Referee for the World Twenty20 in West Indies. The other Match Referees for the tournament are Ranjan Madugalle and Alan Hurst. Crowe is the reserve Match Referee for the event.    
